Justice driven from carth by the wickedness of man was enshrined in heaven as the constellation Virgo. The story is borrowed from Aratus (Pham. 96-136)‚ by whom it was expanded from Hesiod (Op. 200). It is just possible, however, that Virgil may have identified the Hesiodic figure with the “virgin ’' of Jewish prophecy as con- cerned in the coming epoch.
